Moelis Appoints Five Directors to Global Advisory Board

-- B y   A m b e r e e n   C h o u d h u r y
-- 
2011-06-28T08:15:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/moelis-appoints-five-directors-to-global-advisory-board-1-.html
Moelis & Co., the investment bank
founded by Kenneth Moelis, started a global advisory board with
five directors to provide advice across financial markets.  The board will include Charlene Barshefsky, a former U.S.
trade representative, and Hubert Vedrine, a former French
foreign minister, New York-based Moelis said in a statement
today. Kwon Ping Ho, founder of luxury resorts operator Banyan
Tree Holdings Ltd., Michael Marks, former chairman of
Flextronics, and Sidney Taurel, former Eli Lilly & Co. chairman,
will also sit on the board under the chairmanship of former
Standard Chartered Plc chairman  Mervyn Davies .  To contact the reporter on this story:
